OL,5, The share of wealth owned by the       
OL,6, world's richest people soared during   
OL,7, the Covid pandemic, a major study on   
OL,8, inequality has found.                  
OL,10,FThe World Inequality Report said that  
OL,11,F2020 saw the steepest increase in      
OL,12,Fbillionaires' wealth on record.        
OL,14,FMeanwhile, 100 million people sank into
OL,15,Fextreme poverty, the report from the   
OL,16,FParis-based World Inequality Lab said. 
OL,18,FThe richest 10% of the population now  
OL,19,Ftakes 52% of global income and the     
OL,20,Fpoorest half just 8%, it said.         
